         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/11/65 ¶ Dear Sir Redmond ¶  ¶ I intend, if my departmental means admit, to employ the bearer in my establishment to assist me in getting some vegetable articles prepared for the exhibition. ¶ Presu...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.11.22a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Redmond Barry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">VPRS 5486/PO/3, official inward correspondence, VA 928 Melbourne Public Library, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22/11/65</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir Redmond</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I intend, if my departmental means admit, to employ the bearer in my establishment to assist me in getting some vegetable articles prepared for the exhibition.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presumably the Intercolonial Exhibition of Australasia, Melbourne, 1866.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would be desirable, that Mr Hoffmann, who was assistant to Prof Hoffmann of London, should have access to the various works of technological chemistry in the public library, to read up on some theoretical &amp; practical points. Would you do me the favor of granting him access to the Library in the interest of the exhibition?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 24 November 1865,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Barry instructed: 'Mr Tulk will be so good as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to admit this Gentleman if the state of the Library will allow him to read'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
